ngs-management/listingManagementActions.ts:38:  if (!user) throw new Error(\"Unauthorized\");\nsrc/features/guide/components/listings-management/listingManagementActions.test.ts:28:    auth: {\n./src/features/guide/components/public/public-guides-grid.tsx:75:        intro=\"Найдите проверенного местного гида.\"\n./src/features/guide/components/public/public-guides-grid.tsx:164:              Присоединяйтесь к Provodnik — показывайте свои маршруты путешественникам со всей России.\nsrc/features/guide/components/public/public-guides-grid.tsx:75:        intro=\"Найдите проверенного местного гида.\"\nsrc/features/guide/components/public/public-guides-grid.tsx:164:              Присоединяйтесь к Provodnik — показывайте свои маршруты путешественникам со всей России.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:1:# Tripster → Provodnik Replication Plan\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:3:_Written 2026-04-11 after mapping Tripster's guide side (01), editor schema (02), and traveler side (03). This plan anchors everything to the current Provodnik app state (see gap analysis at the end) and explicitly designs in the bid/request distinction from day one._\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:15:> 9. **Review replies are moderated** — add `review_replies` table with `moderation_status`, submit button text \"Отправить на проверку\".\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:35:Provodnik's **negotiation backbone is already in place**: `traveler_requests` + `guide_offers` + `conversation_threads` (with `subject_type ∈ {request, offer, booking, dispute}`). That's rarer than it sounds — it's exactly the thing Tripster does NOT have. Tripster only has paid bookings on pre-priced listings; their \"Задать вопрос\" inquiry flow is a weak bolt-on inside the booking MFE.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:37:So Provodnik should NOT replicate Tripster wholesale. It should replicate **the listing depth, schedule/availability, editor UX, deposit-only payment, calendar, and order-thread polish** from Tripster — and keep the bid/request flow as the native primary path, with pre-priced instant-book as a secondary path that maps to a one-step bid acceptance. Tours and excursions are both listings that accept bids; excursions additionally accept instant bookings.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:41:## Feature matrix — Tripster × Provodnik × gap\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:43:| # | Tripster feature | Provodnik today | Gap | Priority |\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:66:## Listing-type taxonomy for Provodnik\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:70:| Provodnik type | Maps from Tripster | Accepts bids? | Instant-book? | Multi-day? |\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:186:The thread component needs a system-event row type. Current `messages` table has `body text` and `author_id`. Add a nullable `system_event_type text` column (values: `request_created | bid_submitted | bid_accepted | guide_amended | booking_created | guide_confirmed | booking_completed`) plus a JSON `system_event_payload jsonb` for field-level diffs like Tripster's \"**Стоимость:** 1500 ₽\" strong-highlight. The thread component renders system events as a distinct row type with inline strong diffs. Same component powers request threads, booking threads, and (future) dispute threads.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:255:Copy Tripster's \"Поддержка\" block. Working hours, order number for copy-paste, Telegram/email/phone channels. Cheap, high-value.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:273:- **Mobile app parity** — Tripster pushes the \"download our app\" heavily; Provodnik is web-first for now.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:278:- **Contact-visibility reputation gate for the GUIDE** — Tripster revokes a guide's ability to see traveler contacts on new orders when the guide's conversion rate drops below 60% (\"Контакты можно смотреть от 60%\"). Acts as a spam filter and a performance lever. In Provodnik this would gate the bid-acceptance PII unlock on a guide-conversion floor. Needs reliable conversion-rate accounting before it can be safely applied — don't ship until P1-B stats views are stable.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:281:- **Self-service guide payout history** — Tripster has NO self-service payout surface (accounting handles it out-of-band and guides complain about it). Easy differentiator for Provodnik once commission > 0.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:302:- **ADR-013:** Request → offer → accept → booking is the ONLY v1 booking path. No instant-book variant for any listing type. Rationale: user decision — every booking requires guide confirmation because this is a bid marketplace. Preserves Provodnik's differentiator.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/04-replication-plan.md:314:From the parallel scan of the Provodnik app:\n./src/features/guide/components/excursions/guide-excursions-screen.tsx:50:  const [authenticatedGuideId, setAuthenticatedGuideId] = useState<Uuid | null>(null);\n./src/features/guide/components/excursions/guide-excursions-screen.tsx:83:        } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./src/features/guide/components/excursions/guide-excursions-screen.tsx:84:        if (!user) throw new Error(\"Unauthorized\");\n./src/features/guide/components/excursions/guide-excursions-screen.tsx:294:        <GuidePortfolioScreen guideId={authenticatedGuideId ?? \"\"} />\nsrc/features/guide/components/portfolio/guide-portfolio-screen.test.tsx:29:  it(\"loads portfolio photos for the authenticated guide instead of trusting the prop id\", async () => {\nsrc/features/guide/components/portfolio/guide-portfolio-screen.test.tsx:32:      auth: {\nsrc/features/guide/components/portfolio/guide-portfolio-screen.test.tsx:34:          d