\n./src/features/guide/components/verification/verification-upload-form.tsx:169:              ? \"Обязательные документы загружены. Можно отправлять профиль на проверку.\"\r\n./src/features/guide/components/verification/verification-upload-form.tsx:177:          {isSubmitting ? \"Отправляем...\" : \"Отправить на проверку\"}\r\n./src/features/guide/verification-actions.ts:53:    if (msg.includes(\"Не авторизован\") || msg.includes(\"Unauthorized\")) {\r\n./src/features/guide/verification-actions.ts:84:  } = await supabase.auth.getSession();\r\n./src/features/guide/profile-actions.ts:29:    error: authError,\n./src/features/guide/profile-actions.ts:30:  } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./src/features/guide/profile-actions.ts:31:  if (authError || !user) return { ok: false, error: \"Требуется вход\" };\n./src/features/guide/profile-actions.test.ts:14:    auth: { getUser: mockGetUser },\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:1:# Provodnik Pre-Launch QA — Master Execution Plan\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:29:- [ ] 1.2 \"Создать запрос\" CTA → `/traveler/requests/new` (should redirect to auth)\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:31:- [ ] 1.4 Guide acquisition CTA → `/auth/signup`\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:40:- [ ] 1.11 \"Стать гидом\" → `/for-guides` or `/auth/signup`\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:41:- [ ] 1.12 \"Создать запрос\" → auth redirect\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:85:- [ ] 1.42 Bid-first CTA: \"Запросить у этого гида\" → auth redirect\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:90:- [ ] 1.45 Unauthenticated: sees \"Войти чтобы присоединиться\"\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:96:### `/auth`\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:102:### `/auth/signup`\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:111:- [ ] 2.1 Navigate to `/auth/signup`\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-plan.md:147:- [ ] 4.1 Navigate to `/auth/signup`\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.test.tsx:148:      auth: {\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.test.tsx:213:  it(\"uses auth.getUser() rather than auth.getSession() for guide identity\", () => {\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.test.tsx:222:    expect(source).toContain(\"auth.getUser()\");\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.test.tsx:223:    expect(source).not.toContain(\"auth.getSession()\");\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/public-page-unification-opus-task.md:4:Unify Provodnik public pages into one coherent product experience. Pages should keep separate user intents, but share the same visual language, layout rhythm, search/filter treatment, card shell, spacing, and page family rules.\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/public-page-unification-opus-task.md:15:- Preserve Provodnik brand colors and existing design tokens.\n./docs/qa/2026-04-14-audit-findings.md:6:an authenticated end-to-end workflow with 4 test users completing the full\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/bid-form-panel.test.tsx:22:    auth: { getUser: async () => ({ data: { user: { id: \"guide-1\" } } }) },\nsrc/features/guide/components/requests/bid-form-panel.test.tsx:22:    auth: { getUser: async () => ({ data: { user: { id: \"guide-1\" } } }) },\nsrc/features/guide/components/requests/use-guide-catalog.ts:22:      const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/use-guide-catalog.ts:22:      const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./docs/qa/2026-05-10-e2e-spec-rot-fix.md:10:Six e2e specs in `tests/e2e/tripster-v1/` (`01-create-listing` through `06-dispute-flow`) were authored 2026-04-12/13 against an imaginary fixture set. None of them have ever been runnable against any real DB — the seed accounts they reference don't exist with those credentials.\n./docs/qa/2026-05-10-e2e-spec-rot-fix.md:12:Phase 4 fixed only the auth-page selector pattern (`[name=\"email\"]` → `#email`). Three layers of rot remain.\n./docs/qa/2026-05-10-e2e-spec-rot-fix.md:18:The seed migration `supabase/migrations/20260331121000_phase1_auth_seed_accounts.sql` creates exactly three users:\n./docs/qa/2026-05-10-e2e-spec-rot-fix.md:37:Auth page error confirms: `signInWithPassword` returns \"invalid login credentials\" → the friendly error \"Неверный email или пароль.\" renders → form stays on `/auth` → `waitForFunction(!startsWith(\"/auth\"))` times out.\n./docs/qa/2026-05-10-e2e-spec-rot-fix.md:54:The auth page uses shadcn `<Input id=\"...\" />` controlled-state pattern (no `name=` attr emitted). Internal forms across the app likely follow the same pattern. The specs use `[name=\"...\"]` selectors that won't match.\n./docs/qa/2026-05-10-e2e-spec-rot-fix.md:101:1. **Spike: get one spec green end-to-end against prod.** Pick `04-booking-confirm` (no `name=` selectors, simplest interaction). Get auth working with the real fixture, fix testids or replace with role/label, prove the loop.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:17:**Implication for Provodnik:** the homepage search input is a destination autocomplete + popular-destinations dropdown only. Date + guest filters live on the destination page, not on the home hero. One widget less to build.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:29:**Implication for Provodnik:** we do NOT need to build a generic `/notifications` surface with a bell + popover + read/unread tracking across event types. Counts on the existing sidebar links + per-order unread chips + the 3D preference matrix is the full model. One fewer route + one fewer component.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:53:**Implication for Provodnik:** our request/bid flow maps 1:1 — a `traveler_request` is the inquiry shape, and bids extend it. The toggle from `Задать вопрос` → `Заказать` happens when the traveler accepts a bid, not when they switch tabs. We don't need two forms.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:63:| Provodnik §06 mapping | Real Tripster `exp_type` code |\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:209:**Resubmit flow:** guide clicks `Редактировать` on the catalog card → lands in standard editor → makes changes → saves → hits `Отправить на проверку` → back to moderation queue. **There is no explicit \"resubmit\" button or distinct state.** It's just editing a draft.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:211:**Implication for Provodnik:** v1 needs (a) `moderation_status` + `moderation_reason` on listings, (b) a rejection banner on the catalog card with the two text templates, (c) the editor can reuse the normal save flow — no dedicated resubmit surface needed.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:224:**Implication for Provodnik:** currency is account-scoped. When rendering prices, read `user.display_currency` + apply FX. No header widget to build. Our v1 can hardcode RUB display; per-user currency is P2.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:254:**Implication for Provodnik:** `/help` is a single long page with a search box + 5 collapsible categories + anchor deep-links. Admin-editable via a simple `help_articles(id, section_slug, anchor, title, body_md, order)` table.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:278:- **Submit button:** `Отправить на проверку` (NOT `Опубликовать`)\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:308:**Implication for Provodnik:** v1 can ship single-overall rating to save scope, but the DB should carry the 4 columns from day one so we can backfill the breakdown UI in v1.1 without a migration.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:364:   - Moderated review replies with `Отправить на проверку` flow (§9)\n./docs/product/research/tripster/07-gap-closure.md:389:**3 of 8 listing types are still inference-only** (activity / waterwalk / masterclass). **1 tour editor sub-children capture is partial.** Everything else is directly probed. This is sufficient to clone all functionality in theory, adjusted to Provodnik's locked v1 scope (no payments, no deposits, bid-first, no cancellation, 0% commission).\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:120:        } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:138:    const { data: authSub } = supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange(\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:144:          } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./src/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:154:      authSub.subscription.unsubscribe();\nsrc/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:120:        } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\nsrc/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:138:    const { data: authSub } = supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange(\nsrc/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:144:          } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\nsrc/features/guide/components/requests/guide-requests-inbox-screen.tsx:154:      authSub.subscription.unsubscribe();\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:38:**Implication for Provodnik:** the guide account has three legal surfaces: self-identity (passport/INN), per-region licenses (аттестация), and tour operator registry (only for multi-day tour sellers). Our current `guide_verification_status` is one bit; we need to split it along these three axes if we plan to ship tours.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:59:**Implication for Provodnik:** notification preferences are a 3D tensor — role × event × channel. Don't flatten it. Our `notification_preferences` JSON should key by role first.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:90:**Implication for Provodnik:** if we need charts, we can do the same thing with Metabase or a lightweight embedded BI. Don't build charting in React. Log events to a reporting schema and point a BI tool at it.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:100:**Implication for Provodnik:** not worth copying in v1, but a cheap reputation+learning loop worth parking in P2.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:113:**Crucially:** there is NO self-service guide-payout dashboard anywhere in the Tripster UI. Guides don't see a \"your next payout is N ₽ on date D\" surface. Payouts are handled out-of-band by the accounting team based on the order table. This is a significant gap from a guide-UX perspective that Provodnik could fill cheaply in P1.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:115:**Implication for Provodnik:** v1 has 0% commission so neither system is needed. Park the affiliate program at P2+. When we do payouts, build a self-service payout history surface; Tripster doesn't have one and their guides complain about it in forum posts.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:121:**Implication for Provodnik:** add a `listing_favorites(user_id, listing_id, created_at)` table + heart toggle on listing cards. Cheap P1 win.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:141:**Implication for Provodnik:** three referral mechanisms are possible (partner/affiliate, traveler-to-traveler, guide-to-traveler). V1 doesn't need any. Park at P2.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:168:**Implication for Provodnik:** our home page needs 3 rails at minimum — destinations, guides, seasonal/editorial. The offer-count badges on the region rail are a strong trust signal and trivial to compute. The editorial curation (seasonal rail + feature-collage) is expensive to maintain but not essential for v1 — can be driven from a `homepage_sections` DB table managed by admin.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:188:**Implication for Provodnik:** copy the taxonomy to our help center. Six categories covers 90% of traveler questions. Put it at `/help/` with a search box and route support email to a shared inbox. V1 doesn't need a ticketing system.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/05-management-surfaces.md:203:**Implication for Provodnik:** our v1 drops 3 of these states (no payment → no `Ждёт оплаты`, no `Внесена предоплата`; no cancellation → no `Отменён` path). V1 surfaces only `Ждёт подтверждения → Забронирован → Завершён`. See ADR-017.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/03-traveler-side.md:172:| User message | \"{author name} / {date} / {body}\" | \"Гилян / 9 ноя 2025 / 1250 руб, заказ 5844859\" |\n./docs/product/research/tripster/03-traveler-side.md:181:- H3 \"Поддержка\"\n./docs/product/research/tripster/03-traveler-side.md:188:## Takeaways for Provodnik\n./docs/product/research/tripster/03-traveler-side.md:192:2. **Single-page booking form with deposit-only collection** — not a multi-step wizard, not a Stripe-style split checkout. The form creates the order row first; payment widget opens on the resulting `/order/{id}/` detail page. For Provodnik this means the booking form itself doesn't need to embed a payment provider — payment is a second step that only runs if the guide accepts.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/03-traveler-side.md:194:3. **PII gate tied to order state.** Exact meeting point, guide phone, guide email are hidden until the traveler pays the deposit (and re-hidden if the order is cancelled/completed). This is a deliberate friction point that funds the platform. Adopt it for Provodnik so guides can't route travelers off-platform before a deposit lands.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/03-traveler-side.md:202:7. **Payment-recipient labelling as trust signal.** The constant \"Платежи гидов Трипстеру\" label on every order row/header/card reinforces that Tripster handles money. A similar \"Оплата через Provodnik\" chip everywhere we collect money is cheap trust infrastructure.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/06-listing-type-matrix.md:3:_Researched 2026-04-11. Maps what the editor shows/hides across Tripster's 8 listing types, based on direct probing of `experience` (draft 115859) and `MULTIDAY_TOUR` (tour 61998 detail page). This is the file that drives §P0-B editor branching rules for Provodnik._\n./docs/product/research/tripster/06-listing-type-matrix.md:20:| Code | Russian | Provodnik mapping (per ADR-014) |\n./docs/product/research/tripster/06-listing-type-matrix.md:136:**Finding:** Tripster's `deposit_rate` is a per-listing field, defaulting from type (tours tend to 15%, excursions 25%) but guide-overridable. For Provodnik v1 this is moot — no deposits — but if we ship payments in v2 we must store `deposit_rate` on `listings`, not on a global config.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/06-listing-type-matrix.md:152:**Implication for Provodnik:** `guide_profiles.average_rating` and `listings.average_rating` must be maintained independently. Rating aggregation jobs write to both. Listing cards show listing rating; detail pages show both.\n./docs/product/research/tripster/06-listing-type-matrix.md:154:## Implications for Provodnik §P0-B editor\n./docs/product/research/tripster/06-listing-type-matrix.md:204:The data model is a superset keyed by `exp_type`. The editor hides sections it doesn't need and swaps the schedule-and-pricing leaves for the type's dedicated variant. Provodnik can do the same with one `ListingEditor` shell + a `SECTIONS_BY_TYPE` map + a handful of type-specific leaf components (`TourDaysEditor`, `TransferPickupEditor`, `ExcursionScheduleEditor`). Don't build three separate editors — build one and branch.\n./src/features/guide/components/bookings/guide-bookings-screen.tsx:28:    const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();\n./src/features/guide/components/bookings/guide-bookings-screen.test.tsx:27:      auth: {\n./docs/product/research/tripster/02-editor-schema.md:345:## Key architectural takeaways for Provodnik\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/navigation-unification-opus-task.md:4:Create one reusable role-based navigation system for Provodnik so public, traveler, guide, and admin nav surfaces use a shared source of truth and consistent behavior.\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/navigation-unification-opus-task.md:160:- admin `/admin/dashboard` if seeded auth is available; otherwise document blocker.\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:7:    \"title\": \"Запросы — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:151:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:576:    \"title\": \"Запросы — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:720:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:1145:    \"title\": \"Экскурсии — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:1289:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:1698:    \"title\": \"Экскурсии — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:1842:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2251:    \"title\": \"Гиды — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2395:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2766:        \"text\": \"ГидыНайдите проверенного местного гида.Поиск гида\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2814:        \"text\": \"Вы гид?Присоединяйтесь к Provodnik — показывайте свои маршруты путешественникам со всей России.Стать\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2829:    \"bodyText\": \"«Проводник»\\nЗапросы\\nЭкскурсии\\nГиды\\nНаправления\\nКак это работает\\nСтать гидом\\nВойти\\nГиды\\n\\nНайдите проверенного местного гида.\\n\\nПоиск гида\\n\\nТемы:\\n\\nИстория и культура\\nПрирода\\nГастрономия\\nИскусство\\nНеобычные маршруты\\nНочные прогулки\\nАктивный отдых\\nВодные прогулки\\nРелигия и духовность\\nТимур Сафин\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Татарский, Английский · 7 лет в туризме\\nГастрономия\\nИстория\\nСемейные маршруты\\nНовый гид\\nАнна Белова\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Английский · 8 лет в туризме\\nАрхитектура\\nКультура\\nФотопрогулки\\nНовый гид\\nМария Гречко\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Английский · 10 лет в туризме\\nПрирода\\nЕда\\nСемейные поездки\\nНовый гид\\nБаатр Манджиев\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Калмыцкий, Английский · 9 лет в туризме\\nБуддийская культура\\nИстори\"\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2836:    \"title\": \"Гиды — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:2980:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3351:        \"text\": \"ГидыНайдите проверенного местного гида.Поиск гида\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3399:        \"text\": \"Вы гид?Присоединяйтесь к Provodnik — показывайте свои маршруты путешественникам со всей России.Стать\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3414:    \"bodyText\": \"«Проводник»\\nГиды\\n\\nНайдите проверенного местного гида.\\n\\nПоиск гида\\n\\nТемы:\\n\\nИстория и культура\\nПрирода\\nГастрономия\\nИскусство\\nНеобычные маршруты\\nНочные прогулки\\nАктивный отдых\\nВодные прогулки\\nРелигия и духовность\\nТимур Сафин\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Татарский, Английский · 7 лет в туризме\\nГастрономия\\nИстория\\nСемейные маршруты\\nНовый гид\\nАнна Белова\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Английский · 8 лет в туризме\\nАрхитектура\\nКультура\\nФотопрогулки\\nНовый гид\\nМария Гречко\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Английский · 10 лет в туризме\\nПрирода\\nЕда\\nСемейные поездки\\nНовый гид\\nБаатр Манджиев\\nПроверен\\nРусский, Калмыцкий, Английский · 9 лет в туризме\\nБуддийская культура\\nИстория\\nГородские прогулки\\n5,0\\n1 отзыв\\n1 поездка\\n100% рекомендуют\\nДмитрий Ко\"\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3421:    \"title\": \"Направления — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3565:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3884:        \"text\": \"Поддержка\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3904:        \"text\": \"НаправленияОткройте города и регионы России — и найдите местного гида в каждом из них.\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3935:    \"bodyText\": \"«Проводник»\\nЗапросы\\nЭкскурсии\\nГиды\\nНаправления\\nКак это работает\\nСтать гидом\\nВойти\\nНаправления\\n\\nОткройте города и регионы России — и найдите местного гида в каждом из них.\\n\\nПоиск направления\\nculture\\n4.9\\n\\nЭлиста\\n\\n3 гидов\\n6 экскурсий\\ncity\\n4.8\\n\\nМосква\\n\\n1 гидов\\n2 экскурсий\\nculture\\n4.9\\n\\nКазань\\n\\n1 гидов\\n1 экскурсий\\nnature\\n4.9\\n\\nСочи\\n\\n1 гидов\\n1 экскурсий\\nculture\\n5\\n\\nСанкт-Петербург\\n\\n1 гидов\\n1 экскурсий\\n\\nО ПРОЕКТЕ\\n\\nКак это работает\\nДоверие и безопасность\\nСтать гидом\\nДля бизнеса\\n\\nПОДДЕРЖКА\\n\\nПомощь\\nTelegram-поддержка\\nEmail: support@provodnik.app\\n\\nОтвечаем ежедневно, обычно в течение нескольких часов (с 9:00 до 22:00 МСК).\\n\\nПРАВИЛА\\n\\nУсловия использования\\nКонфиденциальность\\nCookies\\n\\nМЫ В СЕТИ\\n\\nОператор пер\"\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:3942:    \"title\": \"Направления — Provodnik\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:4086:        \"href\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:4405:        \"text\": \"Поддержка\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:4425:        \"text\": \"НаправленияОткройте города и регионы России — и найдите местного гида в каждом из них.\",\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/hermes/metrics.json:4456:    \"bodyText\": \"«Проводник»\\nНаправления\\n\\nОткройте города и регионы России — и найдите местного гида в каждом из них.\\n\\nПоиск направления\\nculture\\n4.9\\n\\nЭлиста\\n\\n3 гидов\\n6 экскурсий\\ncity\\n4.8\\n\\nМосква\\n\\n1 гидов\\n2 экскурсий\\nculture\\n4.9\\n\\nКазань\\n\\n1 гидов\\n1 экскурсий\\nnature\\n4.9\\n\\nСочи\\n\\n1 гидов\\n1 экскурсий\\nculture\\n5\\n\\nСанкт-Петербург\\n\\n1 гидов\\n1 экскурсий\\n\\nО ПРОЕКТЕ\\n\\nКак это работает\\nДоверие и безопасность\\nСтать гидом\\nДля бизнеса\\n\\nПОДДЕРЖКА\\n\\nПомощь\\nTelegram-поддержка\\nEmail: support@provodnik.app\\n\\nОтвечаем ежедневно, обычно в течение нескольких часов (с 9:00 до 22:00 МСК).\\n\\nПРАВИЛА\\n\\nУсловия использования\\nКонфиденциальность\\nCookies\\n\\nМЫ В СЕТИ\\n\\nОператор персональных данных: команда проекта Проводник. Контакт по вопросам обраб\"\n./docs/qa/finish-website-2026-06-28/discovery-forensics/discovery-clean-refactor-opus-task.md:91:Adjust only if it preserves Provodnik tokens and works across all pages.\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-one-pager.html:6:    <title>Provodnik Investor One-Pager</title>\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-one-pager.html:328:            <p class=\"hero-copy\">Provodnik is built for the part of the category incumbents do not organize well enough: <strong>custom traveler demand</strong>, <strong>budget-led group formation</strong>, and <strong>regional supply still selling through manual channels</strong>. The model combines listings with request-driven booking, structured guide offers, trust controls, and a target commission of <strong>10% to 15%</strong>.</p>\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-one-pager.html:335:<div class=\"proof-item\"><strong>24%+ vs 10-15%</strong><span>Sputnik8 public commission versus Provodnik target take rate.</span></div>\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-one-pager.html:348:            <div class=\"lead\"><strong>Problem:</strong> travelers struggle to find the right excursion for budget, dates, format, and trust; guides rely on expensive aggregators or fragmented offline channels.<br /><br /><strong>Wedge:</strong> Provodnik is not another catalog. It is a <strong>request-first marketplace</strong> where travelers can create demand, join others into groups, and receive structured offers from verified guides.<br /><br /><strong>Why this can win:</strong> lower commission matters only when paired with new demand capture. Provodnik competes on liquidity for <strong>custom and budget-sensitive demand</strong>, not on listing breadth alone.</div>\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-one-pager.html:365:<div class=\"point\"><div class=\"point-num\">2</div><div class=\"point-copy\"><strong>Provodnik targets the less organized motion:</strong> traveler requests, budget-led group economics, and local guide supply outside polished catalog systems.</div></div>\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-one-pager.html:377:          <div class=\"footer-mark\">Provodnik · Executive Investor Summary</div>\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-ru.json:3:    \"title\": \"Provodnik Investor RU\",\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-ru.json:9:    \"hero\": \"Provodnik — мобильный маркетплейс экскурсий и туров по России, который закрывает ту часть рынка, где спрос и предложение до сих пор плохо оцифрованы: Telegram-чаты, звонки, личные договоренности, ручной сбор групп и дорогие агрегаторы с высоким take rate.\",\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-ru.json:21:        \"copy\": \"Публичная комиссия Sputnik8 — 24% и выше. Целевой take rate Provodnik — 10–15%.\"\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-ru.json:42:    \"thesis_body\": \"<strong>1. Спрос подтвержден рынком.</strong> Крупные игроки уже доказали наличие спроса, доверительных механизмов и готовности пользователей платить за бронирование экскурсий онлайн.<br /><br /><strong>2. У incumbents есть слабое место.</strong> Они сильны в listing-first логике, но заметно слабее в custom demand, бюджетных сценариях и user-led group formation.<br /><br /><strong>3. Wedge Provodnik понятен.</strong> Пользователь создает запрос по датам, бюджету и формату, другие путешественники могут присоединиться, а гиды отвечают структурированными офферами.<br /><br /><strong>4. GTM дисциплинированный.</strong> Запуск с 1–3 регионов и низкорисковых категорий позволяет сначала доказать ликвидность, а не размывать операционную фокусировку.\",\n./docs/business/investor/provodnik-investor-ru.json:87:  \"footer_mark\": \"Provodnik · Investor RU PDF\"\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:94:    \"route\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:97:    \"finalUrl\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:98:    \"h1\": \"Найдите проверенного местного гида\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:104:    \"screenshot\": \"docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/public-_auth-1280.png\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:106:      \"redirected to auth\"\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:111:    \"route\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:114:    \"finalUrl\": \"/auth\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:115:    \"h1\": \"Найдите проверенного местного гида\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:121:    \"screenshot\": \"docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/public-_auth-375.png\",\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:123:      \"redirected to auth\"\n./docs/qa/page-refactor-audit-2026-06-28/summary.json:128: